{
  "texts": [
    "The system provides feedback at multiple levels: words, sentences, and paragraphs.",
    "At the lexical level, it detects improper word usage using subword segmentation and context embedding, offering synonym suggestions.",
    "At the sentence level, the self-attention mechanism analyzes grammar and proposes alternative expressions.",
    "At the paragraph level, the hierarchical attention model evaluates thematic consistency and logical coherence, suggesting strategies for overall improvement.",
    "The system also incorporates three key personalization features: First, it adjusts feedback priorities based on the learner's error history, such as enhancing tense error detection for students who frequently make such mistakes."
  ]
}